iv><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Is it just me or are we writing about new CAR-T every =
week now? As a reminder, CAR-T cell therapies involve genetically modifying=
 a patient's T cells to express chimeric antigen receptors (CARs) that spec=
ifically target and eliminate cancer cells. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, =
64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Now, rese=
archers have developed a new CAR-T cell therapy using a mutation from cance=
r cells, enhancing their ability to destroy tumors in mice without turning =
cancerous themselves. The new methodology enhances the effectiveness of CAR=
-T cells by incorporating a specific mutation, originally identified in can=
cerous T cells, into the CAR-T cells themselves. This mutation involves the=
 CARD11&#8211;PIK3R3 protein, which significantly boosts the CAR-T cells' a=
bility to infiltrate tumors and sustain their cancer-fighting activity over=
 time. By borrowing this trait from cancer cells, the modified CAR-T cells =
become more potent and durable in their response, allowing them to effectiv=
ely target and destroy tumor cells, even in cases where traditional CAR-T c=
ell therapies have failed.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size=
: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The mutated CAR-T cells sho=
wed significant potency against both blood and solid tumors, potentially im=
proving treatment outcomes in those specific areas. We&#8217;re still just =
working with mice here, but this methodology could offer new hope for treat=
ing cancers that are resistant to current treatments.</p><p style=3D"color:=
 rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">=
<span>Cancer is incredibly challenging to beat. Siddhartha Mukherjee calls =
it &#8220;</span><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/9f3dbf61-8757=
-466d-b6df-a1f69c2b16c6?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbq=
Osa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: unde=
rline;">The Emperor of All Maladies</a><span>.</span></em><span>&#8221;</sp=
an><em> </em><span>But we&#8217;re heartened by the variety and sophisticat=
ion of new approaches scientists are throwing at the emperor, from CAR-T to=
 screening. Yesterday, our friends at </span><a href=3D"https://substack.co=
m/redirect/4dc1e673-6e19-4641-8499-ba4d16f20917?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J=
5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64=
); text-decoration: underline;">Ezra</a><span> </span><a href=3D"https://su=
bstack.com/redirect/bb048d7b-a7f7-4cd0-89e9-82c967640192?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3=
QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(6=
4, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">announced $21 million in fresh fun=
ding</a><span> to make early detection the norm. Early detection + new tool=
s to use against the cancers we detect could be a potent combination.  </sp=
an></p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;"><hr style=3D"back=
